<paragraph blockId="20.[264,1324,399,1825]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Etymology. This species is named 
<emphasis box="[727,815,1719,1744]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blahnik Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[727,810,1719,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Alterosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="escova">escova</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
from the Portuguese word for brush, referring to the somewhat brush­like preanal appendages of this species. The word is used as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
